      "href": "/tilapia/list/daddy-issues/",
      "user": "tilapia",
      "slug": "daddy-issues",
      "title": "Daddy issues",
      "desc": "Came to think of a thing when I watched the weird, intruiging \"The Orphan\" last night at a friend's - why is it that psycho thrillers about characters with \"mummy issues\" feels hackneyed and banal (an easy, overrused plot for bad psycho killer movies) while films about characters with \"daddy issues\" almost always feel so interesting, haunting and special?\n\nI don't know, but I do know there are too damn few of these films, so let's get together and make a list of this little mini-genre!",
